'''Abstemious''', ''<code>[[adjective (part of speech)|adjective]]</code>'' [L. ''abstemius''; ''ab'', ''abs'' + root of ''temetum'' [[intoxicating]] drink.]

<ol>
<li>[[Abstaining]] from wine. [Orig. Latin sense.]

<code>Under his special eye ''Abstemious'' I grew up and thrived amain. ''[[Milton (source)|Milton]].''</code>

<li> [[Sparing]] in diet; [[refraining]] from a free use of food and strong drinks; [[temperate]]; [[abstinent]]; [[sparing]] in the [[indulgence]] of the appetite or passions.

<code>Instances of longevity are chiefly among the ''abstemious''. ''[[Arbuthnot (source)|Arbuthnot]].''</code>

<li> [[Sparingly]] used; used with [[temperance]] or [[moderation]]; as, an ''abstemious'' diet. ''[[Gibbon (source)|Gibbon]].''

<li> Marked by, or [[spent]] in, [[abstinence]]; as, an ''abstemious'' life.

<code>One ''abstemious'' day.</code> ''[[Pope (source)|Pope]].''

<li> [[Promotive]] of [[abstemiousness]]. [R.]

<code>Such is the virtue of the ''abstemious'' well. ''[[Dryden (source)|Dryden]].''</code>
</ol>